The steps to writing code for Matlab for this system are as follows:

1. Define the parameters of the model, including r, K, a, D, and C.

2. Set up the spatial grid, defining the size of the grid and the resolution.

3. Define initial conditions for y(x,y,0) and x(x,y,0), which can be random or specified.

4. Set up the time grid, defining the time step and the total simulation time.

5. Define the functions f(y,x) and g(y,x) that describe the reaction terms.

6. Use finite difference methods to discretize the partial differential equations, using a centered difference for the second derivative and an explicit method for time stepping.

7. Solve the discretized equations iteratively using a loop over time steps.

8. Visualize the results as a function of time and space, using plots or animation.

The code for Matlab for this system can be written as follows:

% Define parameters
r = 0.1; %intrinsic growth rate
K = 1; %carrying capacity
a = 0.05; %effect of information density on growth rate
D = 0.2; %diffusion coefficient for population
C = 0.1; %diffusion coefficient for information

% Set up grid
N = 50; %number of grid points in each dimension
h = 1/N; %spatial resolution
x = linspace(0, 1, N+1); %define x grid
y = linspace(0, 1, N+1); %define y grid
[xx,yy] = meshgrid(x,y); %make 2D grid

% Define initial conditions
y0 = rand(N+1,N+1); %random distribution
x0 = zeros(N+1,N+1); %no initial information
% x0 = ones(N+1,N+1)*0.5; %uniform distribution

% Set up time grid
dt = 0.01; %time step
T = 10; %total simulation time
t = 0:dt:T; %time vector
nt = length(t); %number of time steps

% Define reaction terms
f = @(y,x) r*y.*(1 - y/K);
g = @(y,x) a*x;

% Initialize solution arrays
yvals = zeros(N+1,N+1,nt);
xvals = zeros(N+1,N+1,nt);
yvals(:,:,1) = y0;
xvals(:,:,1) = x0;

% Solve equations iteratively
for i = 2:nt

    % Finite difference method for diffusion terms
    Lapy = (yvals(1:end-2,:,i-1) - 2*yvals(2:end-1,:,i-1) + yvals(3:end,:,i-1))/h^2 ...
        + (yvals(:,1:end-2,i-1) - 2*yvals(:,2:end-1,i-1) + yvals(:,3:end,i-1))/h^2;
    Lapx = (xvals(1:end-2,:,i-1) - 2*xvals(2:end-1,:,i-1) + xvals(3:end,:,i-1))/h^2 ...
        + (xvals(:,1:end-2,i-1) - 2*xvals(:,2:end-1,i-1) + xvals(:,3:end,i-1))/h^2;

    % Compute reaction terms
    fy = f(yvals(:,:,i-1),xvals(:,:,i-1));
    gx = g(yvals(:,:,i-1),xvals(:,:,i-1));

    % Update solution using explicit method
    yvals(:,:,i) = yvals(:,:,i-1) + dt * (fy + D*Lapy);
    xvals(:,:,i) = xvals(:,:,i-1) + dt * (gx + C*Lapx);

end

% Visualize the results
figure;
for i = 1:nt
    surf(xx,yy,yvals(:,:,i));
    colormap(jet);
    view(2);
    shading interp;
    title(sprintf('t = %.2f', t(i)));
    caxis([0 1]);
    colorbar;
    drawnow;
end

figure;
for i = 1:nt
    surf(xx,yy,xvals(:,:,i));
    colormap(jet);
    view(2);
    shading interp;
    title(sprintf('t = %.2f', t(i)));
    caxis([0 1]);
    colorbar;
    drawnow;
end

