x = zeros(1, N);

5. Implement the partial differential equations as finite difference approximations. For the logistic growth model, we can use the centered difference approximation for the spatial derivatives:

yxt = r * y .* (1 - y/K) + D * (circshift(y,1) - 2*y + circshift(y,-1)) / (dx^2);

For the linear model, we can use the forward difference approximation for the spatial derivative:

xxt = a * x + C * (circshift(x,-1) - x) / dx;

6. Define the boundary conditions. For periodic boundary conditions, we need to enforce the periodicity at the ends of the grid by wrapping around the values:

