To implement the reaction-diffusion model for human population growth with the specified constraints in MATLAB, we can use the finite difference method to approximate the spatial derivatives, and the built-in ODE solver `ode45` to solve the time derivatives. Below is MATLAB code that you can use as a starting point:

```matlab
% Parameters
r = 1;
K = 1000;
a = 0.01;
m = 0.1;
D = 1;
b = 0.05;
c = 0.02;

% Discretization
Nx = 100; % Number of grid points for space
Nt = 1000; % Number of time points
L = 10; % Domain length
x = linspace(0, L, Nx)';
dx = x(2) - x(1);
dt = 0.1;
